    "recap_headline": "West Virginia University",
    "recap_text": "WACO, Texas\u00a0\u2013\u00a0The West Virginia University baseball team dropped its Big 12 opener, 7-6, Friday evening at Baylor. The Mountaineers fall to 11-4 overall while the Bears improve to 11-6.\nGraduate student\nSean Smith\nwent 3-for-4 with a home run, his second of the season. Sophomore\nMatt Ineich\nadded his second home run of the season as well and reached base four times.\nOn the mound, junior\nDawson Montesa\ngot the start and allowed three runs in the 3.0 innings while graduate student\nReese Bassinger\nsuffered the loss with three runs allowed in an inning of work. Sophomore\nMac Stiffler\nhad a strong outing, striking out three in 1.2 scoreless innings.\nBaylor jumped out to a 1-0 lead in the second before the Mountaineers evened the score in the third.\nIn the fourth, WVU took the lead with three runs as juniors\nArmani Guzman\nand\nTyrus Hall\neach bunted home a run. Sophomore\nGavin Kelly\ncapped the inning with an RBI single. However, the lead was short-lived as the Bears scored five in the home half to jump back in front.\nAfter Baylor added another run in the fifth, Smith hit a solo home run in the sixth to cut the deficit back to two. Ineich cut the Bears lead to one with a home run in the ninth, but the rally for WVU stopped there.\nThe Mountaineers will look to even the series on Saturday with first pitch from Baylor Ballpark set for 3 p.m. ET.\nFor more information on the Mountaineers, follow @WVUBaseball on\nTwitter\n,\nFacebook\n, and\nInstagram\n."
